//go:build ignore

// AI key setup
// ============
// The AI study features (Explain / Analyze context / Analyze translation) call
// Google Gemini with a single app-owned key. Provide it in ONE of two ways:
//
//   1. Env var (best for development):
//        export GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...
//      Then run/build normally — no file needed.
//
//   2. Embedded key (for packaged builds):
//      Copy this file to `ai_key.go` (which is git-ignored), remove the
//      `//go:build ignore` line at the top, and paste your key below. It gets
//      compiled into the binary.
//
// Get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
//
// NOTE: an embedded key ships inside the app binary and can be extracted, and all
// usage bills to / shares the rate limits of that one key. That's fine for personal
// or small-group builds; move to a hosted proxy (swap geminiAPIKey/newGeminiClient
// in ai.go) before any wide public release.

package holybible

func init() {
	embeddedGeminiKey = "AIza...replace-me..."
}
